Suspected Boko Haram insurgents have raided Madagali 26 people were feared killed and several others were critically injured in Adamawa state.  Locals  confirmed, the gunmen riding motorcycles invaded  Kudakaya village, by 7:00 pm on Monday.  “I saw many corpses while several others critically injured and taken to hospital,”.  Abawu Maina Ularamu a former Madagali local government   chairman sadded that, The attackers burnt several shops and many homes and looted food stuffs.   ‘’ As I am talking to we are living in an atmosphere of despair and agony for this attack, over 20 were killed, while many injured and rushed to hospital.  ‘’ There is no doubt the attackers came from Sambisa. We experience such periodic attacks from Boko Haram, who usually look for food.  ‘’Already residents are fleeing for fear of uncertainty; they (Boko Haram) are not far away with us, any slide opportunity they may strike again,’’ said he.   SP Othman Abubakar, Police Imanage maker in the state who confirmed the attack said he could not establish the causality figure from the attack.  “I was briefed that, insurgents  have attacked the village, though I am yet to get the casualty figures, security operatives were deployed are on the top of the situation.” he maintained”